Guided to the Path of Shadows<br>
-------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
I beg your excuse for my hubris in revealing my past when one such as i has not fully proved oneself, but i offer it up as a testamonial to our leaders, Subati and Selilya for opening my mind to the glory that is Innoruuk. I shall keep my tale short so as to not hinder your other duties. It starts simply enough in a lowly abode in the foriegn quarter of neriak, my father was a blacksmith of modest means and my mother was a baker of fine pastries. I was an only child, one more devoted to my books than to my childhood peers. I loved finding the secrets in those old, musty tomes but did not realize it was Innoruuk's hand guiding my learning. I learned much about the magic arts and pressed the ogre customers whom my father served for any information, but little, if any use, came from those conversations. I was happy, but sheltered also, and so was totally unprepared when tragedy struck. My mother became deathly ill, from what i do not know, and seeing her fair visage crumble in decay brought forth a surge of hate that i had never felt before. I know now that it was Innoruuk himself lending me his power, through some unknown fashion i cured my mother of her disease and realized my calling lay with the priesthood. Bidding farewell to my family, though i still have fondness for them, i left that cozy home to don the robes of and initiate into the priesthood of Innoruuk. I happily delved into the learning afforded me and made many friends there, most notably the gate guards, Javin and Evin, who had seen more of the world and always found a willing ear to listen to their tales in me. One day after i had just successfully finished my testing to be of the 8th rung, i went to my friends to share the good news and perhaps celebrate over a flagon of ale, when what to my shocked eyes should appear but a party of high elfs and erudites and gnomes assaulting my friends at the gate! Alas my skills were not sufficient to save my friends from their fatal injuries and as i wept over their loss, that mangy party of curs spit on their broken bodies and laughed at my weak attempts to challenge them. &quot;Bah &quot;, they said, &quot; tis only a lowly healer, and not a very good one at that, he couldn't even save his friends, Hahahaha!&quot; Those words are burned into my soul and i vowed to one day exact revenge for my fallen comrades. It was in this state of rage and grief and hate that our leader Subati found me. Ah but that meeting was was surely devised by Innoruuk himself, as i found in Subati a hate and rage that exceeded my own at what had happened, and I knew that this was a man Innoruuk himself had blessed. Subati was then joined by the fair Selilya and proceeded to instruct me as to the ways of the Harvest. It was then that i realized i had found a purpose to my life and with great reverance and joy accepted Subati's invitation to join his family. I have found my life's work now and hope to follow in the path of Innorruk and prepare this world for his coming under the exhalted leadership of the Harvest.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.showPrevMessage?topicID=23.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.showNextMessage?topicID=23.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/harvest/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.emailToFriend?topicID=23.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fvhbrellfrm3.threadControl?topicID=23.topic><img src=http://home.columbus.rr.com/harvest/s